  "slug": "black-pudding-hash",
  "title": "Black Pudding Hash",
  "subtitle": "Crispy fried black pudding with crushed potato and fried egg, a proper breakfast or brunch plate",
  "excerpt": "Black pudding hash is a pan-fried mixture of crushed boiled potato and crumbled black pudding, cooked until deeply coloured and served with a fried egg. It is a proper full British breakfast element, served as a standalone plate.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British breakfast tradition. Regional British black pudding use in Bury, Lancashire and the north of England. Contemporary British brunch culture.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "hash",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4ukg000160v4soy4tr8n"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " works best with cold potato. If the potatoes are still warm from boiling, they will stick to the pan and disintegrate rather than forming a crust. Boil them ahead or use leftover potatoes from yesterday.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Use a good ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "black pudding",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4ujh000060v4o6d92svr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": Bury or Stornoway if you can find them. Cheap black pudding tends to fall apart during frying rather than crisping at the edges.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
